20the%20United%20States%20in%20more%20than%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20case%20is%20about%20the%20future%20of%20the%20internet%20and%20whether%20Google%20will%20ever%20face%20meaningful%20competition%20in%20search%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Justice%20Department%20lawyer%20Kenneth%20Dintzer%20as%20the%20United%20States%20government%20began%20making%20its%20case%20against%20the%20tech%20titan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%2010-weeks%20and%20with%20dozens%20of%20witnesses%20called%20to%20the%20bar%2C%20Google%20will%20try%20to%20persuade%20Judge%20Amit%20P.%20Mehta%20that%20the%20case%20brought%20by%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20is%20without%20merit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGoogle%20has%20for%20decades%20innovated%20and%20improved%20its%20search%20engine%2C%20plaintiffs%20escape%20this%20inescapable%20truth%2C%26quot%3B%20Google's%20lawyer%20John%20Schmidtlein%20argued%20before%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHeld%20in%20a%20Washington%20courtroom%2C%20the%20trial%20is%20the%20first%20time%20US%20prosecutors%20have%20tackled%20a%20big%20tech%20company%20head-on%20since%20Microsoft%20was%20targeted%20more%20than%20two%20decades%20ago%20over%20the%20dominance%20of%20its%20Windows%20operating%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20for%20Washington%20DC%2C%20I%20think%20we%20have%20the%20highest%20concentration%20of%20blue%20suits%20in%20any%20location%20here%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20Mehta%20joked%2C%20observing%20the%20dozens%20of%20lawyers%20packed%20into%20his%20courtroom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Google%20case%20centers%20on%20the%20government's%20contention%20that%20the%20tech%20titan%20unfairly%20gained%20its%20domination%20of%20online%20search%20by%20forging%20exclusivity%20contracts%20with%20device%20makers%2C%20mobile%20operators%20and%20other%20companies%20that%20left%20rivals%20no%20chance%20to%20compete.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDintzer%20told%20Judge%20Mehta%20that%20Google%20pays%20out%20%2410%20billion%20every%20year%20to%20Apple%20and%20others%20to%20secure%20its%20search%20engine%20default%20status%20on%20phones%20and%20web%20browsers%2C%20thereby%20burying%20upstarts%20before%20they%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20this%20created%20what%20the%20government%20calls%20a%20%26quot%3Bfeedback%20loop%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20Google's%20dominance%20grew%20ever%20bigger%20because%20of%20its%20monopolist%20access%20to%20user%20data%20that%20rivals%20could%20never%20match.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThrough%20this%20feedback%20loop%2C%20this%20wheel%20has%20been%20turning%20for%20more%20than%2012%20years.%20It%20always%20turns%20to%20Google's%20advantage%2C%26quot%3B%20Dintzer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20dominance%20has%20made%20Google%20parent%20Alphabet%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20richest%20companies%2C%20with%20search%20ads%20generating%20nearly%2060%20percent%20of%20the%20company's%20revenue%2C%20dwarfing%20income%20from%20other%20activities%20such%20as%20YouTube%20or%20Android%20phones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20track%20what%20Google%20did%20to%20maintain%20its%20monopoly...%20It's%20not%20about%20what%20it%20could%20have%20done%20or%20should%20have%20done%2C%20it's%20about%20what%20they%20did%2C%26quot%3B%20Dintzer%20told%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20Court%20'cannot%20intervene'%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20firmly%20rejected%20the%20US%20case%20saying%20that%20its%20search%20engine%20was%20successful%20because%20of%20its%20quality%20and%20the%20huge%20investments%20made%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20court%20cannot%20intervene%20in%20the%20market%20and%20say%20'Google%20you%20are%20not%20allowed%20to%20compete.'%20That%20is%20anathema%20to%20US%20antitrust%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20Google's%20Schmidtlein%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESchmidtlein%20insisted%20that%20testimony%20from%20executives%20at%20Apple%20and%20others%20will%20demonstrate%20that%20Google%20won%20the%20coveted%20default%20status%20on%20iP