%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3Deded47f0fe5bf37ab41c573cd18fa0bd29d12cf57a32f2521cb4ac5cb30181d5%26postID%3D64ff619777744faa55c8cd43%26postSlug%3Dnew-planet-habitability-discoveries-nasa-james-webb-space-telescope-2023-9%26site%3Dbi%26u%3Dhttps%253A%252F%252Fwww.nature.com%252Farticles%252Fs41586-021-03804-9.epdf%253Fsharing_token%253DaMvAzNSKTDpeQ_Lx50lBO9RgN0jAjWel9jnR3ZoTv0OiHZ7kRMaxJS4ikXfsEfuhWNXQC4W7SsC52JCjUDnSSqLC5BhXbWxxUcFJQ3KnlmY6LAuQF02dgmfPAEQqFuQhHT7iq8uOqnhGqUWJGAFWKU9xwVrg8ofZtBSQm0hNMoQ%25253D%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bconfidence%20of%20life%20detection%26quot%3B%20(CoLD)%20scale%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20rank%20the%20strength%20of%20evidence%20for%20alien%20life%20on%20a%20scale%20of%20one%20(weak)%20to%20seven%20(strong).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20level%20one%20at%20most%2C%20Madhusudhan%20said.%20It%20may%20not%20even%20make%20the%20scale%20at%20all%20unless%20another%20set%20of%20observations%20finds%20the%20same%20signal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221722%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22illustration%20cartoon%20shows%20people%20in%20white%20lab%20coats%20building%20a%20staircase%20of%20green%20bricks%20with%20numbers%201%20through%207%20climbing%20it%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63ee9889b66c280019d776d6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20illustration%20of%20the%20CoLD%20scale%20for%20determining%20confidence%20in%20a%20detection%20of%20alien%20life.%3Cp%3ENASA%2FAaron%20Gronstal%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20more%20work%20is%20required%20before%20envisaging%20the%20possibility%20of%20alien%20life%2C%20beginning%20by%20a%20beyond-all-reasonable-doubt%20confirmation%20of%20the%20presence%20of%20DMS%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Doriann%20Blain%2C%20who%20has%20previously%20studied%20K2-18%20b%20at%20the%20Max%20Planck%20Institute%20for%20Astronomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMadhusudhan%20agrees.%20He%20hopes%20to%20publish%20new%20results%20from%20fresh%20Webb%20observations%20by%20this%20time%20next%20year%2C%20providing%20more%20evidence%20either%20for%20or%20against%20the%20presence%20of%20DMS%20on%20K2-18%20b.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20discovery%20is%20the%20kind%20that%2C%20if%20it%20survives%2C%20you%20will%20look%20at%20it%2010%20years%20from%20now%20and%20say%2C%20well%2C%20that's%20where%20it%20all%20started%2C%26quot%3B%20Madhusudhan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWebb%20solves%20the%20'missing%20methane'%20mystery%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20clear%20in%20the%20data%2C%20and%20groundbreaking%20in%20its%20own%20right%2C%20is%20that%20Webb%20detected%20methane%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20of%20K2-18%20b.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20discovery%20solves%20a%20decade-long%20%26quot%3Bmissing%20methane%26quot%3B%20problem%2C%20in%20which%20astronomers%20knew%20there%20should%20be%20methane%20in%20certain%20planets'%20atmospheres%20but%20they%20just%20couldn't%20find%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFinding%20methane%20is%20important%20because%20it%20contains%20carbon%2C%20which%20is%20a%20foundational%20element%20for%20life%20as%20we%20know%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20the%20most%20basic%20thing%20that%20we%20are%20saying%20%E2%80%94%20that%20we%20found%20carbon-based%20molecules%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20huge%20revolution%20in%20the%20field%2C%26quot%3B%20Madhusudhan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConfirming%20these%20findings%20requires%20a%20lot%20more%20observation%20of%20K2-18%20b.%20Over%20the%20course%20of%20the%20next%20year%2C%20Madhusudhan%20has%20time%20scheduled%20with%20Webb%20to%20observe%20the%20planet%20more%2C%20as%20does%20another%20team%20of%20astronomers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWebb%20spotted%20molecules%20in%20the%20planet's%20atmosphere%20that%20Hubble%20couldn't%20see%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%202.6%20times%20the%20size%20of%20Earth%2C%20and%208.6%20times%20its%20mass%2C%20K2-18%20b%20is%20not%20the%20type%20of%20planet%20that%20scientists%20traditionally%20consider%20when%20they're%20looking%20for%20alien%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20%26quot%3Bsub-Neptune%26quot%3B%20or%20a%20%26quot%3Bmini-Neptune.%26quot%3B%20Its%20interior%20is%20probably%20filled%20with%20ice%2C%20rather%20than%20rock.%20As%20Blain%20put%20it%3A%20%26quot%3BK2-18%20b%20is%20not%20exactly%20an%20Earth%20twin.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20previous%20observations%20of%20this%20planet%2C%20with%20the%20Hubble%20Space%20Telescope%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwater-vapor-on-potentially-habitable-super-earth-exoplanet-2019-9%5C%22%3Ehinted%20that%20it%20could%20have%20water%20vapor%20in%20its%20atmosphere%3C%2Fa%3E.%20That%20was%20intriguing%20enough%20that%20Madhusudhan%20and%20his%20collaborators%20peered%20at%20it%20with%20Webb%20earlier%20this%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20starlight%20passes%20through%20K2-18%20b's%20atmosphere%2C%20the%20molecules%20in%20the%20air%20there%20will%20absorb%20some%20wavelengths%20of%20light%20and%20reflect%20others.%20By%20analyzing%20which%20wavelengths%20make%20it%20through%20and%20shine%20at%20Earth%2C%20across%20the%20infrared%20spectrum%20of%20light%2C%20Webb%20can%20identify%20the%20unique%20%26quot%3Bspectral%26quot%3B%20fingerprints%20of%20different%20compounds%20in%20the%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWebb%20can%20analyze%20those%20spectra%20in%20much%20higher%20resolution%20than%20Hubble.%20The%20results%2C%20shared%20on%20Monday%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fgoddard%2F2023%2Fwebb-discovers-methane-carbon-dioxide-in-atmosphere-of-k2-18b%5C%22%3ENASA%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20European%20Space%20Agency%2C%20were%20clear%3A%20There's%20probably%20carbon%20dioxide%20and%20methane%20in%20that%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22chart%20showing%20spectra%20of%20starlight%20from%20planet%20k2-18%20b%20that%20indicate%20carbon%20dioxide%2C%20methane%2C%20and%20possibly%20dimethyl%20sulfide%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ffa70a112d1600192d59d3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESpectra%20of%20K2-18%20b%2C%20obtained%20with%20Webb%E2%80%99s%20NIRISS%20(Near-Infrared%20Imager%20and%20Slitless%20Spectrograph)%20and%20NIRSpec%20(Near-Infrared%20Spectrograph)%2C%20display%20an%20abundance%20of%20methane%20and%20carbon%20dioxide%20in%20the%20exoplanet%E2%80%99s%20atmosphere%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20possible%20detection%20of%20a%20molecule%20called%20dimethyl%20sulfide%20(DMS).%3Cp%3EIllustration%3A%20NASA%2C%20CSA%2C%20ESA%2C%20R.%20Crawford%20(STScI)%2C%20J.%20Olmsted%20(STScI)%2C%20Science%3A%20N.%20Madhusudhan%20(Cambridge%20University)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fesawebb.org%2Fmedia%2Farchives%2Freleases%2Fsciencepapers%2Fweic2321%2Fweic2321.pdf%5C%22%3Efindings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20are%20set%20to%20be%20published%20in%20the%20Astrophysical%20Journal%20Letters%2C%20put%20a%20new%20type%20of%20planet%20on%20the%20map%20in%20the%20search%20for%20alien%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMini-Neptunes%20haven't%20been%20considered%20the%20best%20alien-life%20candidates%20in%20the%20past%2C%20but%20they%20seem%20to%20be%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fexoplanets.nasa.gov%2Fwhat-is-an-exoplanet%2Fplanet-types%2Fneptune-like%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emost%20common%3C%2Fa%3E%20type%20of%20planet%20in%20our%20galaxy.%20Now%2C%20with%20Webb's%20power%2C%20astronomers%20can%20see%20exactly%20what's%20in%20their%20atmospheres.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20opens%20up%20other%20possibilities%2C%26quot%3B%20Eliza%20Kempton%2C%20an%20astronomer%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Maryland%2C%20who%20specializes%20in%20the%20spectra%20of%20exoplanet%20atmospheres%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20the%20first%20sub-Neptune-sized%20planet%20to%20show%