i%3E%3Cli%3ECFPB%20Director%20Rohit%20Chopra%20said%20an%20adverse%20ruling%20could%20risk%20protections%20for%20homeowners.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHousing%20groups%20also%20warned%20of%20chaos%20in%20the%20industry%20if%20CFPB's%20funding%20is%20upended.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20nation's%20highest%20court%20is%20about%20to%20hear%20arguments%20in%20a%20case%20that%20could%20have%20major%20implications%20for%20homeowners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20October%203%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-debt-relief-borrowers-cfpb-scotus-2023-9%5C%22%3Ewill%20take%20on%20the%20case%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau%20v.%20Community%20Financial%20Services%20Association%20of%20America%20Ltd.%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20brought%20on%20by%20payday%20lenders%20to%20challenge%20the%20funding%20structure%20of%20the%20federal%20watchdog%20Consumer%20Financial%20Protection%20Bureau.%20The%20lenders%20took%20issue%20with%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20CFPB%20is%20funded%20by%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%2C%20rather%20than%20having%20to%20rely%20on%20annual%20funding%20approval%20from%20Congress%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20Fifth%20Circuit%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felizabeth-warren-blasts-fifth-circuit-cfpb-funding-unconstitutional-student-loans-2022-10%5C%22%3Eruled%20last%20year%20that%20the%20structure%20is%20unconstitutional%3C%2Fa%3E%20saying%20Congress%20did%20not%20intend%20for%20the%20CFPB%20to%20bypass%20the%20annual%20appropriations%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20the%20question%20rests%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%E2%80%94%20and%20CFPB%20Director%20Rohit%20Chopra%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.consumerfinance.gov%2Fabout-us%2Fnewsroom%2Fprepared-remarks-of-cfpb-directo-rohit-chopra-at-the-mortgage-collaborative-national-conference%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20during%20a%20Monday%20speech%20at%20the%20Mortgage%20Collaborative%20National%20Conference%20that%20an%20adverse%20ruling%20could%20upend%20the%20housing%20industry%20and%20put%20homeowners%20at%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20since%20the%20CFPB%20was%20formally%20established%20in%202011%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%202008%20recession%20%E2%80%94%20during%20which%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chicagofed.org%2Fpublications%2Fchicago-fed-letter%2F2016%2F370%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enearly%204%20million%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%20lost%20their%20homes%20%E2%80%94%20it%20implemented%20standards%20to%20ensure%20borrowers%20who%20take%20on%20mortgages%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20repay%20them.%20It%20also%20established%20new%20rules%20mandated%20by%20Congress%20that%20intended%20to%20%26quot%3Bstop%20systemic%20abuse%20from%20spreading.%20Mortgage%20servicers%20can't%20send%20borrowers%20on%20a%20wild%20goose%20chase%20when%20they%20ask%20for%20help%2C%26quot%3B%20Chopra%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20CFPB%20research%2C%20the%20heightened%20rules%20on%20the%20mortgage%20industry%20saved%2026%2C000%20families%20from%20foreclosure%20and%20at%20least%20127%2C000%20more%20borrowers%20from%20delinquency.%20But%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20threat%20to%20the%20CFPB's%20funding%20structure%20%26quot%3Bwould%20raise%20significant%20concerns%20for%20the%20stability%20of%20the%20housing%20market%20and%20the%20financial%20system%20more%20broadly%2C%26quot%3B%20Chopra%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-block-key%3D%5C%224r4m2%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BReverting%20to%20a%20system%20without%20these%20regulations%20would%20create%20uncertainty%20for%20the%20mortgage%20industry%20and%20the%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Chopra%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20even%20putting%20aside%20the%20questions%20about%20existing%20rules%2C%20moving%20to%20a%20world%20where%20the%20future%20of%20housing%20finance%20oversight%20is%20uncertain%20and%20unknown%2C%20including%20the%20number%20of%20years%20we%20would%20be%20living%20under%20such%20mystery%2C%20should%20raise%20serious%20shared%20trepidations%20among%20market%20participants%2C%20financial%20markets%2C%20and%20consumers%20alike.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-block-key%3D%5C%224r4m2%5C%22%3EHe%20also%20noted%20that%20this%20is%20an%20especially%20precarious%20time%20due%20to%20the%20changes%20mortgage%20lenders%20are%20experiencing%2C%20including%20housing%20supply%20shortages%20and%20the%20student-loan%20payment%20resumption%20that%20could%20impact%20housing%20demand.%20The%20Mortgage%20Bankers%20Association%2C%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Home%20Builders%2C%20and%20the%20National%20Association%20of%20Realtors%20expressed%20similar%20sentiments%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.supremecourt.gov%2FDocketPDF%2F22%2F22-448%2F266839%2F20230515120807734_230503a%2520Amici%2520Curiae%2520Brief.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20an%20amicus%20brief%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20support%20of%20the%20CFPB.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-block-key%3D%5C%224r4m2%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BThe%20litigation%20and%20widespread%20uncertainty%20that%20would%20likely%20result%20from%20a%20decision%20that%20suddenly%20called%20all%20the%20CFPB's%20rules%20into%20question%20would%20prove%20devastating%20to%20the%20mortgage%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20groups%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-block-key%3D%5C%222pc2h%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BAny%20freeze%20on%20new%20loans%20would%20devastate%20consumers'%20options%20for%20buying%20or%20selling%20homes%2C%20given%20that%20most%20people%20need%20financing%20to%20purchase%20a%20house%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20continued.%20%26quot%3BAlmost%2080%25%20of%20all%20homebuyers%20use%20a%20loan%20to%20purchase%20a%20home%2C%20and%20among%20first-time%20homebuyers%20that%20number%20jumps%20as%20high%20as%2097%25.%20Not%20only%20would%20first%20time%20homebuyers%20be%20devastated%20by%20an%20inability%20to%20obtain%20a%20mortgage%2C%20but%20minority%20communities%20also%20would%20be%20disproportionately%20negatively%20impacted.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-block-key%3D%5C%222pc2h%5C%22%3EThe%20groups%20also%20said%20that%20the%20economic%20impacts%20of%20an%20adverse%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20would%20be%20widespread%20because%20thousands%20of%20Americans%20who%20work%20in%20the%20mortgage%20industry%20could%20lose%20their%20jobs%20if%20the%20mortgage%20market%20crashes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20data-block-key%3D%5C%222pc2h%5C%22%3EAt%20this%20point%2C%20it's%20unclear%20how%20broadly%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20rule%2C%20and%20if%20it%20will%20strike%20down%20the%20CFPB's%20funding%20structure%20entirely.%20As%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-debt-relief-borrowers-cfpb-scotus-2023-9%5C%22%3EInsider%20previously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%2C%20the%20stakes%20are%20high%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstudent-loan-forgiveness-debt-relief-borrowers-cfpb-scotus-2023-9%5C%22%3Eprotections%20for%20student-loan%20borrowers%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20consumers%20nationwide%20could%20be%20at%20risk%2C%20and%20it%20could%20open%20legal%20challenges%20into%20other%20agencies%20that%20do%20not%20receive%20annual%20funding%2C%20like%20the%20Federal%20Reserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-homeowners-should-worry-cfpb-supreme-court-challenge-housing-market-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694546567000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64b6d19476558a00189d27a1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-homeowners-should-worry-cfpb-supreme-court-challenge-housing-market-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20hear%20a%20case%20that%20could%20upend%20the%20CFPB%2C%20and%20in%20turn%2C%20jeopardize%20the%20housing%20and%20student-loan%20industries%2C%20Rohit%20Chopra%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22asheffey%40businessinsider.com%20(Ayelet%20Sheffey)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A36%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-homeowners-should-worry-cfpb-supreme-court-challenge-housing-market-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Offered%20To%20Fly%20Back%20Justin%20Trudeau%20On%20IAF%20One%20After%20Jet%20Snag%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20offered%20services%20of%20aircraft%20IAF%20One%20to%20Canada's%20Justin%20Trudeau%20after%20his%20special%20aircraft%20developed%20a%20technical%20glitch%20shortly%20before%20his%20departure%20from%20New%20Delhi%20after%20the%20G20%20Summit%2C%20said%20sources.%20According%20to%20Canada's%20National%20Defence%2C%20the%20snag%20involved%20a%20part%20that%20must%20be%20replaced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Canadian%20side%2C%20however%2C%20declined%20the%20offer%20and%20chose%20to%20wait%20for%20the%20backup%20aircraft%2C%20they%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECanadian%20PM%20Trudeau%20and%20his%20delegation%20departed%20from%20the%20national%20capital%20on%20Tuesday%20afternoon%20after%20being%20forced%20to%20extend%20his%20India%20stay%20for%20two%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrudeau%2C%20who%20arrived%20in%20India%20for%20the%20G20%20Summit%20on%20Friday%2C%20had%20to%20extend%20his%20stay%20in%20the%20national%20capital%20after%20a%20technical%20snag%20on%20his%20Airbus%20plane%20on%20Sunday%20night%2C%20prompting%20the%20Canadian%20side%20to%20call%20for%20an%20alternate%20aircraft%20for%20the%20PM%20and%20his%20delegate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20alternate%20aircraft%20that%20was%20expected%20to%20arrive%20in%20Delhi%20on%20Monday%20night%20made%20an%20unscheduled%20diversion%20to%20London%2C%20further%20delaying%20Trudeau's%20India%20departure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20in%20the%20day%2C%20Rajeev%20Chandrasek