e-15-pro-max-plus-apple-watch-series-9-ultra-2-airpods-pro-wonderlust-4382011%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Apple%20event%202023%20begins%20tonight%20and%20the%20company's%20next%20Wonderlust%20event%20will%20start%20at%2010%3A30pm%20IST.%20Four%20new%20handsets%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20unveiled%20in%20the%20iPhone%2015%C2%A0series%20along%20with%20new%20Apple%20Watch%20Series%209%20and%20Apple%20Watch%20Ultra%20models.%20Apple%20is%20also%20expected%20to%20announce%20the%20release%20dates%20for%20iOS%2017%2C%C2%A0iPadOS%2017%2C%C2%A0macOS%2014%2C%C2%A0tvOS%2017%2C%C2%A0watchOS%2010%C2%A0%2C%20and%C2%A0macOS%20Sonoma%C2%A0at%20its%20upcoming%20launch%20event.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A73%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gadgets360.com%2Fmobiles%2Ffeatures%2Fapple-event-2023-launch-iphone-15-pro-max-plus-apple-watch-series-9-ultra-2-airpods-pro-wonderlust-4382011%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-gadgets360-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.gadgets360.com%2Fmobiles%2Ffeatures%2Fapple-event-2023-launch-iphone-15-pro-max-plus-apple-watch-series-9-ultra-2-airpods-pro-wonderlust-4382011%2Famp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gadgets360.com%2Fmobiles%2Ffeatures%2Fapple-event-2023-launch-iphone-15-pro-max-plus-apple-watch-series-9-ultra-2-airpods-pro-wonderlust-4382011%2Famp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Remembering%20the%20Rich%20Life%20Feroze%20Gandhi%20Lived%20Before%20His%20Untimely%20Death%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F12234106%2FFeroze-Gandhi.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EFeroze%20Gandhi%2C%20whose%20111th%20birth%20anniversary%20falls%20today%2C%20was%20a%20freedom%20fighter%2C%20prominent%20parliamentarian%2C%20journalist%20and%20above%20all%2C%20a%20crusader%20against%20corruption.%20He%20was%20only%20forty-eight%20years%20old%20when%20he%20died%20due%20to%20a%20massive%20heart%20attack%20just%20four%20days%20before%20his%20birthday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFeroze%20Gandhi%20was%20born%20on%20September%2012%2C%201912%20in%20Bombay%20(now%20Mumbai)%20in%20a%20Parsi%20family%20from%20Gujarat.%20He%20lost%20his%20father%20when%20he%20was%20hardly%20six%20years%20old%2C%20and%20his%20family%20comprising%20his%20mother%20and%20her%20five%20children%20moved%20to%20Allahabad%20to%20live%20with%20his%20aunt%2C%20who%20was%20a%20surgeon%20in%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20Lady%20Dufferin%20Hospital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20completing%20his%20graduation%20from%20Allahabad%2C%20he%20went%20to%20study%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20(but%20much%20later).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201930%2C%20Feroze%20joined%20the%20independence%20movement%2C%20which%20was%20then%20passing%20through%20the%20phase%20of%20civil%20disobedience%20led%20by%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%2C%20whose%20%3Cem%3Esatyagraha%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20included%20the%20boycott%20of%20English%20education.%20It%20was%20in%20a%20demonstration%20outside%20his%20college%2C%20the%20Ewing%20Christian%20College%2C%20that%20Feroze%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20first%20contact%20with%20the%20already%20well%20known%20Nehru%20family%20happened.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKamala%20Nehru%2C%20the%20wife%20of%20Pandit%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20who%20was%20incarcerated%2C%20was%20leading%20a%20procession%20on%20a%20hot%20summer%20afternoon%20shouting%20slogans%20like%20%E2%80%98Bharat%20%3Cem%3Emata%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Ezindabad%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98Mahatma%20Gandhi%20zindabad%E2%80%99%20when%20she%20fainted%20due%20to%20exhaustion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFeroze%20Gandhi%2C%20who%20was%20was%20witnessing%20the%20demonstration%20with%20his%20classmates%20atop%20a%20wall%20in%20the%20campus%2C%20jumped%20down%20immediately%20and%20helped%20carry%20Kamala%20under%20the%20shade%20of%20a%20tree%20and%20nursed%20her%20to%20recovery.%20This%20chance%20encounter%20was%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20lasting%20relationship%20with%20the%20Nehrus%20that%20only%20ended%20with%20his%20death%2028%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20during%20the%20civil%20disobedience%20movement%20Feroze%20was%20imprisoned%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20Lal%20Bahadur%20Shastri%2C%20who%20also%20hailed%20from%20Allahabad%2C%20was%20amongst%20his%20jail%20companions.%20They%20developed%20an%20intimate%20friendship%20and%20often%20visited%20Anand%20Bhavan%20together%20after%20their%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201961%2C%20a%20year%20after%20Feroze%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%20Shastri%2C%20who%20was%20then%20home%20minister%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.in%2Fbooks%3Fid%3D6KohEAAAQBAJ%5C%22%3Erecalled%20his%20association%20with%20the%20former%3C%2Fa%3E%3A%20%E2%80%9CFeroze%20was%20much%20younger%20than%20I.%20Despite%20that%2C%20we%20became%20very%20close%20friends%2C%20and%20it%20became%20routine%20to%20meet%20and%20go%20on%20for%20hours%20with%20general%20political%20exchange%20of%20ideas%20and%20opinions.%20Very%20few%20people%20at%20the%20age%20of%20seventeen%20or%20eighteen%20show%20such%20a%20devotion%2C%20patriotism%20and%20understanding%20as%20Feroze%20did.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMotilal%20Nehru%2C%20who%20was%20sentenced%20to%20six%20months%20in%20jail%20along%20with%20his%20son%20Jawaharlal%2C%20died%20on%20February%206%2C%201931%2C%20soon%20after%20he%20was%20released.%20At%20his%20funeral%20in%20Allahabad%2C%20Feroze%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20mother%2C%20Rattimai%2C%20met%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20and%20begged%20him%20to%20tell%20Feroze%20to%20give%20up%20political%20activities%20and%20resume%20his%20studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20what%20the%20Mahatma%20replied%20in%20Gujarati%20to%20Rattimai%2C%20who%20was%20a%20Gujarati%20from%20Surat%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COh%20%3Cem%3Ebahen%20%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0if%20I%20get%20seven%20boys%20like%20Feroze%20to%20work%20for%20me%2C%20I%20will%20get%20%3Cem%3Eswaraj%3C%2Fem%3E%20within%20seven%20days.%20In%20the%20India%20of%20the%20future%2C%20nobody%20will%20ask%20whether%20your%20son%20passed%20his%20BA%20or%20MA%2C%20but%20they%20will%20like%20to%20know%20how%20many%20times%20your%20son%20has%20been%20interned%20for%20nationalst%20activities.%E2%80%9D%20The%20words%20of%20the%20Mahatma%20didn%E2%80%99t%20impress%20Rattimai.%20But%20though%20she%20was%20dejected%2C%20she%20decided%20not%20to%20interfere%20in%20Feroze%E2%80%99s%20chosen%20path.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decade%20of%20the%201930s%20was%20an%20eventful%20one%20in%20the%20history%20of%20the%20freedom%20struggle%20and%20in%20the%20Nehru%20household.%20It%20saw%20the%20top%20stalwarts%20of%20the%20Congress%20assume%20presidentship%20after%20the%20Salt%20Satyagraha%20(March%20%E2%80%93%20April%201930)%20%E2%80%93%20Sardar%20Patel%20(1931)%2C%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20(1936%2C%201937)%2C%20Rajendra%20Prasad%20(1934)%20and%20Subash%20Bose%20(1938%2C%201939).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMonths%20before%20Nehru%20became%20Congress%20president%20for%20the%20second%20time%2C%20Kamala%20Nehru%2C%20who%20had%20been%20suffering%20from%20tuberculosis%20for%20long%2C%20died%20in%20a%20sanatorium%20in%20Switzerland.%20Before%20she%20died%20on%20Feb%206%2C%201936%2C%20Kamala%20Nehru%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20given%20her%20consent%20to%20the%20marriage%20of%20her%20daughter%20Indira%20to%20Feroze%2C%20who%20had%20proposed%20to%20her%20three%20years%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20marriage%20ultimately%20was%20solemnised%20as%20per%20Vedic%20rituals%20at%20Anand%20Bhavan%20on%20March%2026%2C%201942%2C%20the%20day%20of%20the%20Ram%20Navami%20festival.%20Since%20it%20was%20an%20inter-faith%20wedding%20in%20those%20days%20of%20extreme%20orthodoxy%2C%20it%20was%20bound%20to%20raise%20a%20major%20controversy.%20It%20was%20especially%20so%20as%20one%20party%20involved%20was%20the%20most%20well-known%20political%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUpper%20caste%20Hindus%20especially%20reacted%20vehemently%3A%20%E2%80%98Brahmin%20girl%20marrying%20a%20Parsi%3F%E2%80%99%20But%20since%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20blessed%20the%20marriage%2C%20the%20controversy%20died%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20nevertheless%20Pandit%20Nehru%20issued%20a%20press%20statement%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20marriage%20is%20a%20personal%20and%20domestic%20matter%20%E2%80%A6%20though%20parents%20may%20and%20should%20advise%20in%20the%20matter%2C%20the%20choice%20and%20ultimate%20decision%20must%20lie%20with%20the%20two%20parties%20concerned%20%E2%80%A6%20it%20is%20no%20business%20of%20parents%20or%20others%20to%20come%20in%20the%20way.%20When%20I%20was%20assured%20that%20Indira%20and%20Feroze%20wanted%20to%20marry%20one%20another%2C%20I%20accepted%20willingly%20their%20decision%20and%20told%20them%20that%20it%20had%20my%20blessing.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENehru%20went%20on%20to%20add%3A%20%E2%80%9CMahatma%20Gandhi%2C%20whose%20opinion%20I%20value%20not%20only%20in%20public%20affairs%20but%20in%20private%20affairs%20also%2C%20gave%20his%20blessings%20to%20the%20proposal%20%E2%80%A6%20%5Bhe%5D%20expressed%20a%20wish%20that%20marriage%20might%20take%20place%20in%20Sevagram%20so%20that%20he%20might%20find%20it%20convenient%20to%20be%20present%20at%20it%20and%20bless%20the%20union%20personally%20%E2%80%A6%20but%20the%20members%20of%20the%20family%20felt%20that%20it%20should%20take%20place%20in%20our%20home.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmongst%20those%20who%20attended%20the%20simple%20and%20unostentatious%20marriage%20ceremony%2C%20in%20which%20a%2024-year-old%20Indira%20wore%20a%20khadi%20saree%20spun%20by%20her%20father%20in%20jail%2C%20were%20Dr%20Rajendra%20Prasad%2C%20Maulana%20Azad%2C%20Govind%20Ballabh%20Pant%2C%20Sarojini%20Naidu%2C%20Syed%20Mahmud%20and%20Acharya%20Kripalani.%20A%20surprise%20guest%20at%20the%20Anand%20Bhavan%20was%20Sir%20Stafford%20Cripps%2C%20who%20had%20arrived%20in%20India%20for%20his%20famous%20Cripps%20Mission%20that%20was%20to%20be%20rejected%20by%20the%20Congress%20Working%20Committee%20(CWC)%20the%20following%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Quit%20India%20Movement%20led%20to%20the%20arrest%20of%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20and%20all%20senior%20leaders%20of%20the%20CWC%20in%20Bombay%20on%20the%20dawn%20of%20August%209%2C%201942.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20was%20taken%20to%20Ahmadnagar%20jail%20along%20with%20Sardar%20Patel%2C%20Maulana%20Azad%20and%20others%2C%20Feroze%20and%20Indira%20Gandhi%20returned%20to%20Allahabad%2C%20and%20after%20carrying%20out%20underground%20activities%20for%20nearly%20a%20month%2C%20were%20arrested%20in%20mid-September%20and%20sentenced%20to%20one%20year%20rigorous%20imprisonment%20in%20Naini%20jail%2C%20where%20once%20again%20Feroze%20found%20the%20company%20of%20Nehru%E2%80%99s%20successor-to-be%20as%20PM%2C%20Lal%20Bahadur%20Shastri.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20Feroze%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20fourth%20and%20last%20term%20in%20jail.%20He%20had%20been%20arrested%20three%20times%20earlier%20in%20the%201930s%20during%20and%20after%20the%20civil%20disobedience%20movement.%20After%20serving%20a%20full%20term%20of%20one%20year%20in%20Naini%20and%20Faizabad%20jails%2C%20Feroze%20was%20released%20and%20went%20back%20to%20stay%20at%20Allahabad%20with%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20who%20had%20been%20released%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlmost%20a%20year%20before%20independence%2C%20an%20interim%20government%20was%20formed%20on%20September%202%2C%201946%20and%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20as%20head%20of%20the%20government%2C%20became%20extremely%20busy%20with%20his%20monumental%20responsibilities.%20He%20had%20founded%20the%20%3Cem%3ENational%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%201937%2C%20but%20now%20after%20it%20resumed%20publication%20in%20early%201946%2C%20he%20realised%20he%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20able%20to%20devote%20time%20for%20the%20paper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20persuaded%20Feroze%20to%20become%20a%20director%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3ENational%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20his%20place.%20Feroze%20Gandhi%20was%20appointed%20as%20the%20managing%20director%20of%20the%20Associated%20Journals%20Limited%2C%20which%20published%20the%20%3Cem%3ENational%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E.%20He%20ran%20the%20paper%20efficiently%20and%20brought%20it%20out%20from%20the%20financial%20difficulties%20it%20was%20facing%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20took%20the%20initiative%20of%20bringing%20out%20the%20Urdu%20and%20Hindi%20editions%20of%20the%20paper%20and%20launching%20it%20from%20New%20Delhi%20in%20addition%20to%20Lucknow%2C%20from%20where%20it%20was%20running%20from%20the%20outset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcknowledging%20his%20contribution%2C%20Nehru%20noted%3A%20%E2%80%9CFeroze%20has%20been%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EHerald%3C%2Fem%3E%20now%20for%20over%20six%20months%20%E2%80%A6%20and%20from%20all%20accounts%2C%20has%20done%20very%20good%20work%20%E2%80%A6%20and%20we%20are%20gradually%20reducing%20our%20liabilities%20%E2%80%A6%20there%20is%20peace%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EHerald%3C%2Fem%3E%20office%20and%20cooperation%20between%20the%20editorial%2C%20managerial%20and%20press%20departments.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20general%20elections%20after%20independence%20were%20held%20in%201952%20and%20Feroze%20Gandhi%2C%20who%20fought%20for%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20from%20Rae%20Bareli%20(now%20being%20represented%20by%20Sonia%20Gandhi)%20won%20by%20a%20massive%20margin.%20He%20was%20re-elected%20from%20the%20same%20constituency%20in%20the%20second%20general%20election%20in%201957.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20during%20these%20two%20terms%20in%20parliament%20that%20he%20became%20a%20national%20figure%20by%20his%20brilliant%20performance%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20House%2C%20taking%20up%20issues%20that%20resonate%20even%20today%2C%20over%20six%20decades%20later.%20His%20maiden%20speech%20in%20parliament%20on%20corruption%20in%20the%20insurance%20companies%20run%20by%20Rama%20Krishna%20Dalmia%20led%20to%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20arrest%20and%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20the%20nationalisation%20of%20the%20insurance%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201958%2C%20he%20raised%20the%20Haridas%20Mundhra%20scandal%20involving%20the%20now-government%20controlled%20LIC.%20This%20caused%20a%20great%20embarrassment%20to%20the%20clean%20image%20of%20the%20government%20and%20led%20to%20the%20resignation%20of%20the%20then-finance%20minister%20T.T.%20Krishnamachari%20(TTK%2C%20as%20he%20was%20popularly%20called%2C%20was%20however%20reinstated%20as%20a%20minister%20after%20the%201962%20general%20elections%20and%20reappointed%20as%20finance%20minister%20in%201964%20when%20Lal%20Bahadur%20Shastri%20took%20over%20as%20PM).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBesides%20the%20finance%20minister%2C%20the%20finance%20secretary%20H.M.%20Patel%20was%20dismissed%20from%20service%20and%20Mundhra%2C%20like%20Dalmia%20earlier%2C%20had%20a%20stint%20in%20jail.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFeroze%2C%20who%20ideologically%20was%20a%20staunch%20socialist%2C%20also%20made%20a%20strong%20case%20for%20the%20nationalisation%20of%20Telco%2C%20as%20the%20company%2C%20according%20to%20figures%20he%20marshaled%20painstakingly%2C%20was%20charging%20nearly%20the%20double%20of%20railway%20engines%20being%20imported%20from%20Japan.%20This%20raised%20a%20stir%20in%20the%20Parsi%20community%20as%20the%20Tatas%2C%20like%20Feroze%2C%20belonged%20to%20the%20same%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Feroze%20was%20earning%20greater%20laurels%20and%20becoming%C2%A0%20more%20and%20more%20popular%2C%20he%20unfortunately%20died%20of%20a%20heart%20attack%20at%20a%20young%20age%2C%20four%20days%20before%20his%2048th%20birthday.%20His%20sudden%20death%20shocked%20the%20whole%20nation%2C%20but%20no%20one%20more%20than%20his%20life%20companion%20Indira%20Gandhi%2C%20then%2043.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20death%20was%20physically%20and%20psychologically%20wounding%20for%20her.%20As%20she%20described%20later%3A%20%E2%80%9CMy%20whole%20mental%20and%20physical%20life%20changed%20suddenly%2C%20my%20bodily%20functions%20changed%20%E2%80%A6%20I%20was%20physically%20ill.%20It%20upset%20my%20whole%20being%20for%20years%20%E2%80%A6%20it%20was%20not%20just%20a%20mental%20shock%2C%20but%20it%20was%20as%20though%20someone%20had%20cut%20me%20in%20two.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGradually%20she%20recovered%20and%20was%20to%20ultimately%20become%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20second%20longest%20serving%20prime%20minister%20after%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20but%20there%20was%20a%20greater%20personal%20tragedy%20in%20store%20for%20her%20twenty%20years%20after%20the%20death%20of%20her%20beloved%20Feroze.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20if%20Feroze%20Gandhi%20had%20not%20died%20so%20early%3F%20The%20%E2%80%98ifs%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98buts%E2%80%99%20of%20history%20will%20remain%20what%20they%20are.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPraveen%20Davar%20is%20an%20ex-Army%20officer%2C%20a%20columnist%20and%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3EFreedom%20Struggle%20and%20Beyond.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694543044000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F12234106%2FFeroze-Gandhi.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fthe-rich-life-feroze-gandhi-lived-before-his-untimely-death%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Feroze%20Gandhi%20was%20a%20freedom%20fighter%2C%20prominent%20parliamentarian%20and%20crusader%20against%20corruption.%20This%20piece%20traces%20the%20various%20threads%20in%20his%20rich%20life%2C%20including%20his%20joining%20the%20Nehru%20family%2C%20before%20his%20untimely%20death%2063%20years%20ago.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22New%20Dress%20Code%20For%20Parliament%20Staff%20Kicks%20Off%20Row%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20Parliament%20building%20is%20all%20set%20to%20host%20its%20first%20session%20on%20September%2018.%20While%20the%20agenda%20of%20the%20special%20session%20is%20still%20unclear%2C%20it%20is%20certain%20that%20the%20parliament%20proceedings%20will%20move%20to%20the%20new%20building%20on%20September%2019%2C%20Ganesh%20Chaturthi.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20the%20revamped%20building%2C%20the%20uniforms%20of%20Parliament%20staff%20will%20also%20be%20new.%20The%20outfit%20has%20been%20designed%20by%20the%20National%20Institute%20of%20Fashion%20Technology%20(NIFT).%20Sources%20close%20to%20the%20development%20suggest%20that%20the%20uniform%20change%20was%20supposed%20to%20happen%20in%20the%20last%20parliament%20session%20but%20could%20not%20be%20done%20for%20some%20reason.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20usual%20bureaucrats'%20band%20gala%20suit%20will%20be%20replaced%20with%20a%20magenta%20or%20deep%20pink%20Nehru%20jacket%20with%20a%20shirt%20of%20a%20similar%20colour%2C%20featuring%20a%20lotus%20flower%20design.%20The%20employees%20will%20be%20seen%20wearing%20khaki-coloured%20pants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFemale%20staff%2C%20however%2C%20will%20be%20seen%20in%20saree%20uniforms%20like%20before.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20marshals%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20and%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20will%20be%20wearing%20a%20Manipuri%20turban%20after%20the%20uniform%20change.%20The%20safari%20suits%20worn%20by%20the%20security%20personnel%20inside%20the%20building%20will%20be%20replaced%20with%20camouflage%20dresses%2C%20similar%20to%20the%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20ahead%20of%20the%20lined-up%20changes%2C%20controversy%20has%20erupted%20over%20the%20use%20of%20Lotus%2C%20which%20also%20happens%20to%20be%20the%20election%20symbol%20of%20the%20ruling%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP).%20Opposing%20the%20move%2C%20Congress'%20Manickam%20Tagore%20said%20that%20instead%20of%20a%20lotus%2C%20the%20designs%20could%20have%20national%20symbols%20like%20peacock%20and%20tiger.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EControversy%20over%20the%20lotus%20theme%20for%20Rajya%20Sabha%20has%20played%20out%20earlier%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20parliament%20building%20was%20inaugurated%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20May%20this%20year.%20Calling%20the%20building%20a%20%26quot%3Btestament%20of%20the%20dawn%20of%20Aatmanirbhar%20Bharat%20(self-reliant%20India)%2C%20PM%20Modi%20added%2C%