Fclimate%2Fcop27_fail_success_of_loss_and_damage%2F%5C%22%3Eloss%20and%20damage%20fund%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20climate-vulnerable%20states%2C%20a%20new%20global%20norm%20has%20emerged%20around%20the%20idea%20of%20wealthier%20countries%20banding%20together%20to%20deliver%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oxfam.org%2Fen%2Fpress-releases%2Fg7-owes-huge-13-trillion-debt-global-south%23%3A~%3Atext%3DIn%2520April%252C%2520the%2520G7%2520agreed%2Cclimate%2520finance%2520goal%2520by%25202025.%5C%22%3Eclimate-related%20assistance%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20the%20Global%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20surprisingly%2C%20climate%20change%20is%20a%20prime%20focus%20of%20the%20summit%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2FImages%2FCPV%2FG20-New-Delhi-Leaders-Declaration.pdf%5C%22%3Ejoint%20statement%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0published%20on%20Saturday.%20The%20%E2%80%9CGreen%20Development%20Pact%20for%20a%20Sustainable%20Future%E2%80%9D%20section%20runs%20to%20eight%20pages%20%E2%80%93%20longer%20than%20any%20other%20topic%20%E2%80%93%20and%20covers%20subjects%20ranging%20from%20clean%20energy%20transitions%20and%20emissions%20cuts%20to%20climate%20finance%20and%20plastic%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2FImages%2FCPV%2FG20-New-Delhi-Leaders-Declaration.pdf%5C%22%3EDelhi%20Declaration%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0still%20falls%20short%20on%20climate.%20It%20features%20extensive%20pledges%20to%20fight%20climate%20change%2C%20but%20most%20don%E2%80%99t%20offer%20specific%20targets%20or%20timeframes.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20document%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20set%20specific%20mitigation%20goals%20and%20targets%20for%20G20%20countries%20themselves.%20Rather%2C%20the%20focus%20is%20more%20on%20contributing%20to%20global%20mitigation%20efforts%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20reiterate%20our%20commitment%20to%20achieve%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eglobal%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0net%20zero%20GHG%20emissions%2Fcarbon%20neutrality%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9CWill%20pursue%20and%20encourage%20efforts%20to%20triple%20renewable%20energy%20capacity%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eglobally%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0through%20existing%20targets%20and%20policies%E2%80%9D%20(emphases%20mine).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20little%20doubt%20that%20the%20varying%20national%20situations%20of%20member%20states%20make%20it%20hard%20to%20set%20common%20goals%20and%20targets%20for%20pursuit%20at%20home.%20But%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20prevent%20the%20G20%20from%2C%20say%2C%20deciding%20on%20separate%20common%20emissions%20reduction%20targets%20for%20developed%20and%20developing%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20inconvenient%20truth%20is%20that%2C%20despite%20genuine%20commitments%20to%20promote%20a%20greener%20planet%2C%20so%20many%20G20%20members%20are%20still%20locked%20into%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Findia-climate-change-g20-cop28-c25dd753a2f8f520261ec4858b921a1a%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAccording%2520to%2520a%2520report%2520by%2Ct%2520have%2520carbon%2520capture%2520technologies.%5C%22%3Eold%20and%20dirty%20energy%20habits%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20lessens%20the%20likelihood%20of%20upholding%20pledges%20on%20curbing%20emissions%2C%20and%20helps%20explain%20why%20many%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Declaration%E2%80%99s%20climate%20commitments%20are%20vague.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20G20%20members%20spent%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.carbonbrief.org%2Fdaily-brief%2Fg20-countries-gave-record-1-4tn-to-support-fossil-fuels-in-2022-report%2F%5C%22%3Erecord%20amount%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20fossil%20fuels.%20According%20to%20energy%20think%20tank%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fember-climate.org%2Finsights%2Fresearch%2Fg20-per-capita-coal-power-emissions-2023%2F%5C%22%3EEmber%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20multiple%20G20%20countries%20saw%20major%20rises%20in%20per%20capita%20emissions%20over%20the%20past%20seven%20years%2C%20including%20Indonesia%20(56%25)%2C%20Turkiye%20(41%25)%2C%20China%20(30%25)%2C%20and%20India%20(29%25).%20Many%20G